## Development Workflow (SDD)

All development follows the 5-phase SDD workflow:

```bash
# Phase 0 — Explore (optional)
/brainstorm "What I want to build"

# Phase 1 — Capture requirements
/define FEATURE_NAME

# Phase 2 — Design architecture
/design .claude/sdd/features/DEFINE_FEATURE_NAME.md

# Phase 3 — Build implementation
/build .claude/sdd/features/DESIGN_FEATURE_NAME.md

# Phase 4 — Archive when done
/ship .claude/sdd/features/DEFINE_FEATURE_NAME.md

# Cross-phase — When requirements change
/iterate .claude/sdd/features/DEFINE_FEATURE_NAME.md "what changed"

# Resume incomplete build
/continuar FEATURE_NAME
```

**Language:** All SDD documents (BRAINSTORM, DEFINE, DESIGN, BUILD_REPORT, SHIPPED) are generated in **Portuguese-BR (pt-BR)**. Code, commands, and file paths remain in English.

